suncertify.services
Class BookResult

java.lang.Object
  suncertify.services.BookResult
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class BookResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The result of an attempted book operation. As the database cannot and should not be locked between subsequent business services operations, the state of the database record at the moment of booking may have changed since the last search operation, and the database record may, in the meantime, have been deleted, updated, or booked by some other agent. These conditions are reflected in the BookResult. Furthermore, the post-booking contractor is also part of the BookResult so that, after an attempted booking request, the respective record may be immediately updated.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Lars Kuettner

BookResult

public BookResult(BookStatus bookStatus,
                  Contractor contractor)
Creates a BookResult object and is the only means of assigning values to the fields.

Parameters:
bookStatus - An enumeration constant representing the status of the booking operation. Due to the concurrent multi-client environment, it is perfectly legal for a booking operation to result in something other than success.
contractor - A Contractor object representing the record field values with which to update the record if booking is possible.
Method Detail

getBookStatus

public final BookStatus getBookStatus()
Provides the status component of the BookResult object.

Returns:
the status enumeration constant indicating whether the record has been successfully booked or not, and if not, why not: because the record has been intermittently grabbed by some other agent, deleted, or modified

getContractor

public final Contractor getContractor()
Provides the Contractor object that reflects the state of the database record under consideration upon return of the booking operation.

Returns:
the Contractor object reflecting the state of the database record after the booking attempt, null on a record that has been intermittently deleted
